					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13133681#post-4587510</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13133681/scp-5499#post-4587510</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2020 15:32:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zimzamble</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1765748</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a pretty well written, short-but-sweet article but I do think it would fit better as a -j.</p> <p>Also I think any uncontained sentient anomaly warrants a Euclid class, the foundation doesn’t know if that consciousness is directly linked to the item or if it’s just acting through it.</p> <p>I think this article would really benefit from an interview log, maybe through giving it different substances and seeing how it reacts and having it slowly realize it doesn’t get to take whatever it wants anymore could be an entertaining punchline for it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
